Release.

The film was released in the United Kingdom on 12 December 2011.

Home media.

The film was released on DVD and Blu-ray on 12 December 2011.

Reception.

Box office.

"Johnny English" grossed $21.7 million in North America and $21.7 million in other territories for a worldwide total of $42.4 million, against a production budget of $30 million.

In the United Kingdom, the film was released on 12 December 2011 and grossed $1.1 million in its opening weekend, finishing in fifth place at the box office.

Results.

By congressional district.

Electors.

Technically the voters of Massachusetts cast their ballots for electors: representatives to the Electoral College. Massachusetts was allocated 15 electors because it had 15 congressional districts and 2 senators. All candidates who appeared on the ballot or qualified to receive write-in votes had to submit a list of 15 electors, who pledged to vote for their candidate and his or her running mate. Whoever won the majority of votes in the state was awarded all 15 electoral votes. Their chosen electors then vote for president and vice president.
